The Herald Cassper Nyovest says he is ready for a boxing rematch against NaakMusiq, after losing to the actor in the ring. On Saturday night, the South African artists went head-to-head in a celebrity boxing match in Sun City. After multiple delays pushed the start of the main fight to after 22:00, NaakMusiq came out victorious. Regardless of the results, #CassperVsNaakMusiq was at the top of Twitter’s trending list, with many praising Nyovest for “reviving a sport that has been longing for media attention”.
Following his fight, the rapper – who has been vocal about his preparations for the fight – called for a rematch with his victorious opponent. “Took an L But we come back stronger. We will hear from the other team when they want da rematch, I say 3 Months would be enough and we get back in. (sic)” he tweeted. Meanwhile, urban publication SlikourOnLife tweeted that a rematch had been confirmed.
With his loss comes an unofficial agreement Nyovest is being called on to follow through. The rapper responded positively to a tweet asking him to be a guest on Podcast and Chill with MacG if he lost. “If I lose the fight with Naak I will go on MacG’s podcast. If I beat Naak though, I’ll never go on that show,” Nyovest replied in February. – Channel24.